The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index advanced the most in
more than 14 months, rising 831.63 points, or 2.9 percent, to
29,490.20 by the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  City Lodge Hotels Ltd. (CLH)  : The hotel operator
releases results for the year to June 30. Basic earnings per
share are expected to be more than 20 percent lower than the
prior year, the group said in a trading statement on June 29.
The stock closed 1.9 percent down at 59 rand.  Impala Platinum Holdings Ltd. (IMP)  : The worldâ€™s second-
largest producer of the metal resumes talks with the National
Union of Mineworkers over wages to avoid a strike, following an
improved offer last week. Shares in the company rose 2.5 percent
to 167.13 rand.  Workforce Holdings Ltd. (WKF)  : The human resources
company releases results for the six months to June 30. Earnings
per share are expected to be 70 percent to 90 percent higher,
the company said in a trading update on Aug. 4. The stock was
unchanged at 43 cents a share.  To contact the reporter on this story:
